Peru Stocks: Cementos Lima, Siderperu, Luz del Sur, Buenaventura

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-03-18T18:39:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-18/peru-stocks-cementos-lima-siderperu-luz-del-sur-buenaventura.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 2:14 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index fell for the fourth day this week,
dropping 0.9 percent to 20,562.36. The MSCI All Peru Capped
Index slid 0.7 percent to 2,872.75.  Construction and energy stocks declined on investor concern
over the crises in Libya and  Japan , said Hernando Pastor, an
analyst at Lima-based Juan Magot y Asociados SAB.    Cementos Lima SA (CEMLIMI1)  (CEMLIMC1 PE), the country’s biggest
cement maker, plunged 5.4 percent to 36.20 soles.  Empresa
Siderurgica del Peru SAA (SIDERC1)  (SIDERC1 PE), a unit of Gerdau SA,
Latin America’s largest steelmaker, fell 3.7 percent to 1.56
soles. Corp. Aceros Arequipa SA (CORAREI1 PE), the Lima-based
steelmaker, dropped 4 percent to 3.12 soles. Luz del Sur
(LUSURC1 PE), Peru’s largest electricity distributor, fell 1.5
percent to 6.70 soles.  Gold and tin miners gained after metals advanced in New
York and  London .    Minsur SA (MINSURI1)  (MINSURI1 PE), the world’s fourth-largest tin
producer, rose 1.8 percent to 3.98 soles. Cia. de Minas
Buenaventura SAA (BVN PE), the country’s biggest precious-metals
miner, gained 1.6 percent to $42.30.  To contact the reporter on this story:  Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  